16/01/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The head of the BiH Police Restructuring Commission, Wilfred Martens, submitted a final report on police reform to High Representative Paddy Ashdown and BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic on Friday (14 January).
Martens told a news conference that the panel offered a concept for the establishment of a single police structure in BiH and state-level control over the sector.
(Nezavisne novine, Dnevni avaz - 15/01/05;
Fena, PBS BiH, RS Government Web site - 14/01/05)
